e Morgan's laws: the negation of a disjunction is logically equivalent to the\nconjunction of the negations. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L545-L546","name":"not_and'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#not_and'","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L543-L543","name":"not_and","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#not_and","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L541-L541","name":"not_and_distrib","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#not_and_distrib","doc":"One of de Morgan's laws: the negation of a conjunction is logically equivalent to the\ndisjunction of the negations. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L536-L537","name":"Decidable.not_and_distrib'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Decidable.not_and_distrib'","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L532-L533","name":"Decidable.not_and_distrib","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Decidable.not_and_distrib","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L528-L529","name":"not_and_of_not_or_not","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#not_and_of_not_or_not","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L522-L524","name":"decidable_of_bool","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#decidable_of_bool","doc":"Prove that `a` is decidable by constructing a boolean `b` and a proof that `b ↔ a`.\n(This is sometimes taken as an alternate definition of decidability.) "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L517-L518","name":"decidable_of_iff'","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#decidable_of_iff'","doc":"Transfer decidability of `b` to decidability of `a`, if the propositions are equivalent.\nThis is the same as `decidable_of_iff` but the iff is flipped. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L512-L513","name":"decidable_of_iff","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#decidable_of_iff","doc":"Transfer decidability of `a` to decidability of `b`, if the propositions are equivalent.\n**Important**: this function should be used instead of `rw` on `decidable b`, because the\nkernel will get stuck reducing the usage of `propext` otherwise,\nand `dec_trivial` will not work. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L506-L506","name":"not_and_not_right","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#not_and_not_right","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L503-L504","name":"Decidable.not_and_not_right","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Decidable.not_and_not_right","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L499-L500","name":"iff_iff_not_or_and_or_not","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#iff_iff_not_or_and_or_not","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/876d9cc42ccbfea023752e40e6edb7279d9c6b5a/Mathlib/Logic/Basic.lean#L493-L497","name":"Decidable.iff_iff_not_or_and_or_not","docLink":"./Mathlib/Logic/Basic.html#Decidable.iff_iff_not_or_and_or_not","do